			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Troll Shaman:<BR>
<BR>
Okay, as you've probably read already, you start out with food, drink, Inner Fire scroll, Minor Healing scroll, and a club.  The first thing to do is scribe and memorize your spells.  Then buff yourself with Inner Fire.  Next go to the guild house and turn in your note.  Put all 5 points into Fishing (it's a great way to make money early on).  Now, hail the Troll you gace the note to and get the quest where you got to turn in 2 Bone Chips and 2 Pieces of Froglok Tad Skin.  Then, go out into Innothule Swamp, and remember to re-buff yourself whenever needed.  Loot everything worth more than 4 copper (looting 1 cp snake fangs is basically pointless) definitely go after Decaying Skeletons they have nice loot, and remember to get the Bone Chips for the quest.  Also kill Froglok Tads they occasionally drop Netted armor (same AC as cloth, magical, fits all) which is up to you whether you want to sell it or wear it.  After you got 2 Bone Chips and 2 Pieces of Froglok Tadpole Skin go back to your guild and turn them in.  You will get the Burst of Flame scroll (DD spell that does 4 damage) this is very useful for pulling monsters.  Now, if you're level 2 (which you probably are) put 5 more points into Fishing.  And, if you have enough money, buy a Fishing Pole and several pieces of bait.  Fishing Poles cost around 2 gold 5 silver; bait costs 4 copper.  Now find a nice place to fish inside the town, since your skill level is 10 your fishing pole will rarely if ever break.  Using fishing I made enough money at level 2 to buy all my 1st level spells and had a lot left over.  It usually goes pretty quick a fish is worth 2 silver and you can also catch things like tattered cloth sandals (1.6 silver), rusty daggers (2.4 silver) and Fish Scales (4 copper).  After you have made quite a bit of money go buy as many spells you can of your level don't waste money on Endure Cold, it is useless to your level.  The 1st level buffs are very good (Dexterous Aura, Strengthen, and Inner Fire) always have them all on at all times.  Now its time to go back into Innothule and 'bash'.  Kobolds give good loot and experience mainly stick to them and of course kill decaying skeletons with weapons.  Don't waste time on 1st level creatures kobolds give 4 or 5 times better experience and a lot better loot.  At level 3 some Frogloks may con blue or white to you kill them of course as well as Froglok Tads and Decaying Skeletons.  Do NOT go to the Froglok islands near Guk, you will get swarmed and killed.<BR>
At level 4 you should go out by Guk, some Froglok Fishermen will con white so kill them and be near the wall at all times so you can run back to the Bashers when things get ugly.  At level 5 you get a new set of spells (you should have been saving up from the time you bought all your level 1 spells, which I think I forgot to mention).  I bought almost all except Endure Fire and Spirit Pouch (which I have no idea what does).  Now you can take most Fungus Man Trackers, Frogloks, Froglok Fishermen, Swamp Alligators, and some Froglok Foragers (don't go looking for these they are too far out but kill one if someone trained it to where you are hunting).  By now, if you havent found one on a decaying skeleton, you may want to procure a Two-Handed Blunt weapon of some sort, they do much more damage than One-Handed Blunt and the delay is worth it.  A worn great staff is usually a good choice and decaying skeletons drop these.<BR>
<BR>
Well until next time I feel like posting, good luck in your 'bashin'.<BR>
<BR>
                      --Phaedo
				</font>
